Sep 23 2009 	Great hotel!	My partner and I stayed at The Baldwin for 2 nights which we booked after reading good reviews on here.The room was plenty big enough for our needs and we were overlooking a street which was nice. I'd read reviews about the lift being noisy but apart from my partner getting stuck half in and half out on our arrival (his fault not the lift!) we didn't notice anything although our room was down the landing from it. The bathroom was fairly small but everything in looked new and it was clean as was the room itself.The staff we dealt with were all very helpful and friendly, allowing us to check in early on arrival and we asked them to recommend a chinese restaurant which they did (probably a relative!) and it was fabulous.The location is ideal - minutes walk from Chinatown and Union Square.The price was also great - far cheaper than staying at Fishermans Wharf.The only (slight) problem we had was with parking - upon arrival we were asked if we needed parking and said yes. They gave us a card and told us it was down the block and first left (Sutter Street) so off we went. When we checked out 2 days later, we found we had gone to the wrong car park (there must be 2 on Sutter Street and the one the hotel use is the second one) - this wasn't a problem for us as we hadn't moved the car but beware if you plan to drive anywhere and make sure you find the right car park as the one were in is charged by the hour. By not moving our car it cost us about $2 less than the hotel were charging for 'their' car park but I'm sure parking in theirs would allow you to take your car in and out for the one standard price (about $25 per day). We had to then go back to the hotel, explain what had happened and were given a refund for their car park (maybe they need to explain in more detail where their car park is in future as we were told we weren't the first to make the mistake but it they are clearly losing revenue by doing this)	
